Specific Requirements and Application Details by Facility/Practice Type
Here are the detailed requirements based on the type of private health practice or facility:
1. Individual Private Practices
•
Who Can Apply:
◦
Applicants must be recognized and registered by their respective councils (NMCB and BHPC) [20b].
◦
Hold required insurances, including Professional and Indemnity insurance [20c, 62].
◦
Must be a resident in Botswana [24n, 55].
◦
Minimum qualification required is a Bachelor's degree (except Nursing/Midwifery where it's a degree or post-basic specialized training) [20a, 53].
◦
Clinical Experience Requirements:
▪
All primary healthcare providers need clinical experience in General Medicine, General Surgery, Paediatrics, and Obstetrics and Gynaecology (beyond internship, not applicable to all cadres) [21f, 53]. Family Physicians are given preference [21f, 54].
▪
Citizen non-specialist practitioners, nursing, and midwifery applicants: Must have worked continuously for five (5) years in clinical practice in Botswana [22g, 54, 60].
▪
Practitioners (specialists and non-specialists), nurses, and midwives who have not been in practice: Must attach themselves to a clinical setting for one (1) year before applying [22h].
▪
Non-citizen specialists: Must have worked continuously for a minimum of five (5) years in Botswana, attached to a Director-recognized facility [23j, 54].
▪
Newly qualified citizen medical and surgical specialists/subspecialists: Must have worked for a minimum of one (1) year in Botswana [23k, 54].
◦
Must provide a declaration of not being a Government or Non-Governmental employee, unless their institution or organization allows it and a letter indicating such is furnished to the Licensing Office [21d, 63].
◦
Must provide a referral pathway to the next level of care [21e, 62].
◦
Applications are assessed considering the existing number of private practices in the area [24m, 61].
◦
Meeting minimum requirements does not guarantee a successful application.
•
Where to Send Application:
◦
All applications must be directed to the Director of Health Services, Ministry of Health, P/Bag 0038 Gaborone, for the attention of the Private Practice Licensing Office.
◦
Applications must be dropped by hand or courier to Office 8A29, 8th floor, Ministry of Health Headquarters.
•
Required Enclosures:
◦
Application letter: Indicating the location of the practice (by town or village), rationale for opening, and envisaged public health benefits [48i].
◦
Certified copy of national identification card (citizens) or passport details (non-citizens) [24o i, 48ii].
◦
Certified copy of residence permit and work permit (non-citizens) or waivers if applicable [25o ii, 48iii].
◦
Certified copies of qualification certificates [48iv].
◦
Current Curriculum Vitae (CV): Must not be more than five pages, showing all pertinent clinical experience, appointments, and work exposure, with no unexplained breaks [25o iv, 49v].
◦
Certified copy of the current BHPC registration (certificate and identity card/blue card) [25o iii, 49vi].
◦
Two (2) recent professional references (not more than six months old), one from the immediate or previous supervisor, with authentication (stamp/letterhead) [25o vi, 49vii].
◦
Confidential reference from the head of the institution where the applicant is/was currently employed: Must be in a sealed envelope, protected from alteration (e.g., marked "CONFIDENTIAL" and sealed/stamped) and articulate issues pertinent to the applicant's ability to work independently, including administrative and disciplinary matters [25o vii, 50viii].
◦
Any other pertinent documentation [51ix].
◦
Consent: By submitting, the applicant consents to the Director of Health Services office obtaining information from previous employers if needed [51x].
•
Special Circumstances:
◦
Radiographers: Must submit a signed mutual agreement with a registered private radiologist attesting that the radiologist will make radiological reporting of the applicant’s medical images [51xi a].
◦
Permissions to engage another practitioner in an existing practice: Requires an application letter from the licence holder indicating motivation (e.g., patient load, access) and includes requirements i-x (except viii) for the new practitioner, plus written consent from the practitioner to be engaged [52xi c, 53].
2. Facilities under Botswana Health Professions Act, 2001 (e.g., Group Practices, Poly-clinics, EMS, Radiology Centres)
•
Who Can Apply: This licence is reserved for citizen healthcare professionals [28a i]. The majority shareholder must be a healthcare professional [28a ii].
•
Where to Send Application:
◦
All correspondence must be addressed to the Director of Health Services, Ministry of Health, Private Bag 0038 Gaborone, for the attention of the Private Practice Licensing Office.
◦
Applications are to be dropped by hand or courier to Office 8A29, 8th floor, Ministry of Health Headquarters.
•
Required Enclosures:
◦
Covering letter: Indicating motivation, location, and need for service [44 1a,b,c].
◦
Proposal: Expected content includes (but is not limited to):
▪
Professional services to be offered [44 2a].
▪
Human resources to be engaged [44 2b].
▪
Structural resources (equipment, buildings, etc.) [44 2c].
▪
Functional clinical governance structure [44 2d].
▪
Envisaged public health benefits [44 2e].
▪
Envisaged equity/equality of services [44 2f].
▪
Innovations [44 2g].
▪
Sustainability plan [44 2h].
▪
Share certifications [44 2i].
▪
Certificates of incorporation [44 2j].
▪
Letters of intent [44 2k].
◦
Other Enclosures:
▪
All credentials of applicants and all parties directly involved [45 3a,b,c].
▪
Curriculum Vitae (CV) of all parties involved [45 3b].
▪
Architectural plans (including alterations for existing structures) [45 3d].
▪
Evidence of land lease [45 3e].
◦
Assessment Criteria: Applicants must demonstrate clear documentation of motivation, evidence of having outgrown a single private practice, a comprehensive plan of public health outcomes and benefits, and capacity to efficiently run the facility [28a iii,iv,v,vi].
•
Licence Validity: The licence for this service is valid for a period of five (5) years.
3. Facilities under Private Hospitals and Nursing Homes Act, 1989
•
Categories: These include medical or surgical hospitals, medical/surgical and maternity hospitals, maternity hospitals, homes for care/accommodation of convalescent or chronically ill persons, hospitals for specified classes of patients/diseases, and rejuvenation centers.
•
Where to Send Application:
◦
The application letter must be addressed to the Honourable Minister of Health, Ministry of Health, Private Bag 0038 Gaborone, for the attention of The Director of Health Services.
•
Required Enclosures:
◦
Covering letter: Indicating motivation, location, and need for service [46 1a,b,c].
◦
Proposal: Expected content includes (but is not limited to):
▪
Professional services to be offered [46 2a].
▪
Human resources to be engaged [46 2b].
▪
Structural resources (equipment, buildings, etc.), including architectural drawings [46 2c].
▪
Functional clinical governance structure [46 2d].
▪
Envisaged public health benefits [46 2e].
▪
Envisaged equity and equality of services [46 2f].
▪
Innovations [46 2g].
▪
Sustainability plan [46 2h].
▪
Share certifications [46 2i].
▪
Certificates of incorporation [46 2j].
▪
Letters of intent [46 2k].